         <abstract>
            <p>A method for computing Legendre functions of integer order and half-odd degree is presented. The method is based on the theory of quadratic transformation of the argument, and is a generalization of Gauss' or Landen's transformation for computing elliptic integrals.</p>
          </abstract>
